description: Fundamentals of Muay Thai and Kickboxing will run through the basics of punching, kicking, throwing knees and combinations as well as the fundamentals of footwork.  We will work on the basics by demonstration and work to hone those skills through shadow boxing and pad work. The class will also include conditioning through circuits, core conditioning, pad work and shadow boxing. Equipment required for beginners are hand wraps and gloves if you have them. For advanced fighters there will be light sparring with gumshields gloves and shin guards.
summary: Muay Thai and Kickboxing Fundamentals - Kickboxing [Physical Activity] MU Life

description: Beginners Aikido Class. We start with some warm up exercises and then move onto some movement drills and falling drills. Following this we will start on some basic techniques. All are welcome!
summary: Aikido Class - Aikido [Physical Activity] MU Life

description: Wednesday sessions for advanced levels will include light sparring, partner drills and pad work, we will work specifically to hone previously gone over combinations and play around with stringing combinations together. We will also work to introduce new techniques both offensive and defensive as well as continuing to develop footwork. Conditioning will include leg and core conditioning. For sparring bring gum shield, wraps, gloves and shin guards. For beginners we will expand on fundamentals and techniques as well as flexibility, mobility and conditioning. Bring hand wraps and gloves if you have them.
summary: Muay Thai and Kickboxing Drills - Kickboxing [Physical Activity] MU Life

description: Wednesday sessions for advanced levels will include light sparring, partner drills and pad work, we will work specifically to hone previously gone over combinations and play around with stringing combinations together. We will also work to introduce new techniques both offensive and defensive as well as continuing to develop footwork. Conditioning will include leg and core conditioning. For sparring bring gum shield, wraps, gloves and shin guards. For beginners we will expand on fundamentals and techniques as well as flexibility, mobility and conditioning. Bring hand wraps and gloves if you have them.
summary: Muay Thai and Kickboxing Drills - Kickboxing [Physical Activity] MU Life

description: Our weekly meet-up at Gravity Climbing Centre in Inchicore. It is great for all levels of bouldering and great way to meet up with fellow climbers in the university. There is the C3 and C4 dublin busses to Memorial gardens and a 20 minute walk. If you have never climbed before, please book a induction at Gravity where the staff will help you learn the basic and how to stay safe while climbing.
